        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 14 at 3:16AM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>The combination of clear skies and temperatures rapidly dropping
into the upper 50s and lower 60s has led to patchy fog formation.
Visibilities are expected to vary greater due to the patchy nature
of the fog, but localized visibilities of one quarter of a mile or
less are possible at times. If travelling, be prepared for rapid
changes in visibilities across short distances and allow extra
following distance with the vehicle ahead of you.
</description>
